    "biography": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Grafvitnir, the Grave-Wolf — Stage 1</strong></p><p><em>Supernatural, Huge • Level 7 Solo • Stamina 200 • Speed 8 • Stability 5 • Free Strike 8 • EV 108</em></p><p>The Grave-Wolf. Níðhöggr’s physical arm. An intelligence of ancient malice, imprisoned in the deepest root-chamber of Yggdrasil since the First Kindling. He is the campaign’s true antagonist — the one who gnaws, who placed agents in the mortal world, who manipulated the Ember-Keepers into voiding their own witnessing rites. He erupts through the floor of Hrafnborg’s great hall in wolf form — sixty, seventy feet long, black fur matted with centuries of Rot, eyes the color of the last thing that burns before it goes dark. He moves toward the Ever-Ember shrine with the specific purpose of something that has been waiting a thousand years.</p><p>Takes 2 turns per round. Has 3 Villain Actions (each once per encounter, max 1 per round).</p>",
      "director": "<p><strong>TACTICAL GUIDANCE — STAGE 1:</strong></p><p>Stage 1 is about positioning and protection. Grafvitnir’s primary objective is the Ever-Ember shrine — he is not trying to kill the party, he is trying to get past them. If the party doesn’t get between him and the shrine, he simply walks past them. The combat is about <em>preventing him from reaching the flame</em>, not defeating him outright.</p><p><strong>Round 1:</strong> Grafvitnir charges the shrine with both turns. VA1 (Howl of Binding) fires at the end of a hero’s turn, coordinating external undead threats.</p><p><strong>Round 2:</strong> The party is learning his two-turn rhythm. VA2 (Lunge) breaks through their formation.</p><p><strong>Round 3–4:</strong> Low Stamina. VA3 (Rot Breath) punishes clustering. All VAs spent. The party pushes through.</p><p><strong>Primordial Resilience:</strong> ALL damage from a single source is capped at 20. This is critical — no single hit can deal more than 20. Tell your players after the first big hit lands.</p><p><strong>Stage Transition:</strong> At 0 Stamina, Grafvitnir collapses and dissolves into the floor. Stage 2 begins on his next turn.</p>",
